NAME

  splice - splice sliced files into a single file

SYNOPSIS

  splice (options)

DESCRIPTION

  splice is designed to concatenate files into a single file using files that
  were created by the slice application.

  The file directory must contain files with a base name containing a period and
  a sequence number (4 digits with leading zeroes).

  The sequence number must begin at 0001.

FLAGS

  -i  [input file path]
  -b  [input file base name]
  -o  [output file name]
  -s  show file names
  -h  display usage
  -v  display version

